state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 4, "created_at": "2022-09-11T11:44:10Z", "updated_at": "2022-09-14T21:19:24Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I tried this code: [godbolt](https://rust.godbolt.org/z/WT4v9Mnar)\r\n\r\n```rust\r\npub fn create_array() -> [Option<u8>; 256] {\r\n    [None; 256]\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI expected to see this happen: This should compile to a memset, or the equivalent unrolled SIMD stores\r\n\r\n[LLVM IR](https://rust.godbolt.org/z/qdG4hPMEc)\r\n\r\nInstead, this happened: It compiles to a bunch of movs.\r\n\r\nI think this happens because we transform this to a bunch of stores of the discriminant, without touching the data part of the option, making it impossible for LLVM to memset this. Ideally, we'd write 0 to the data part as well here, allowing this to use memset.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/101685/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/101685/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}